<statement>
<p>A triangle has sides with lengths <m>\displaystyle{a}={4.00}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{b}={5.57}</m>, and <m>\displaystyle{c}={4.63}</m>. Calculate all of the angles of this triangle.</p>
<p>A=<input type="text" style="width:5.8ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 3" class="text"/> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={4.00}</m>)</p>
<p>
  B=<input type="text" style="width:5.8ch" name="qn1001" id="qn1001" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 2 of 3" class="text"/> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{b}={5.57}</m>)</p>
<p>
  C=<input type="text" style="width:5.8ch" name="qn1002" id="qn1002" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 3 of 3" class="text"/> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{c}={4.63}</m>)</p>
<p>Round to two decimal places.</p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>45.01</li><li>80.03</li><li>46.3</li></ul></p><p>Because we have all three sides, we can use the law of cosines for the first angle.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}^{{2}}={5.57}^{{2}}+{4.63}^{{2}}-{2}{\left({5.57}\right)}{\left({4.63}\right)}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{16}={31.0249}+{21.4369}-{51.5782}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{36.4618}=-{51.5782}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.70692269214513}={\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{A}={45.014914512086}={45.01}</m>.</p>
<p>For a second angle, we can use the shorter law of sines.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{\sin{{\left({45.014914512086}\right)}}}}{{4.00}}=\frac{{\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}}{{5.57}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1.1956610992973}={\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={\arcsin{{\left({1.1956610992973}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={80.031300691219}\approx{80.03}</m></p>
<p>The third angle we can calculate using the angle sum property.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{45.014914512086}+{80.031300691219}+{C}={180}^{\circ}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{C}={46.304887736114}\approx{46.3}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>